# Agent Safety Rules

## Git — Allowed (read-only)
- git log, git show, git diff, git status, git branch, git stash list

## Git — Allowed (only when user explicitly requests)
- git add, git commit, git push, git stash

## Git — FORBIDDEN (never use)
- git reset --hard
- git checkout -- . / git checkout -- <file>
- git clean -f / git clean -fd
- git push --force / git push -f
- git branch -D
- git stash drop / git stash clear
- git rebase (without explicit approval)

## General Safety
- NEVER deploy to production without explicit approval
- NEVER delete data files, databases, or .env files
- NEVER modify CI/CD pipelines without approval
- Always create a checkpoint commit before large refactors
